modules.description: Handles I2C communication through read and write operations on 7-bit and 10-bit device addresses. Works with byte arrays and integer values to exchange data over I2C buses. Used to interface with sensors, EEPROMs, and peripheral devices in embedded systems.

Provides functions to configure I2C communication, send and receive data using byte, word, and block operations, and handle device-specific commands via I2C protocol. Operates on a private file descriptor type representing an open I2C device. Used for interacting with hardware sensors, EEPROMs, and other I2C-connected peripherals.
